cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper deals with privacy concerns in machine learning, specifically in the context of classification models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes solutions for both discrete and continuous data, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of dimensionality reduction techniques, which could place it in cs.DB (Databases) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with statistical estimation, which could also place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
